On Saturday, October 25, 2003, at 06:40 AM, Sage Green wrote:

> How come 2.0 has such a large increase in torque from a 1.8 with a 
> small increase in bore??

Increasing stroke is usually the more effective way to increase torque. 
  Do all of the engines you mentioned have the same stroke?

Another big factor is the camshaft.  Do all of those engines have the 
same cam specs?

